\par\par \b \uc2 Analysis: Capital inflows: Held hostage by global growth outlook\b0\par\par\uc2 612 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 July 2010\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 15\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Harry Su , Bahana Securities,\par \par \uc2 Data flows show that foreigners have been net buyers of all the Asian stock markets since May, with the exceptions of Thailand and the Philippines on the back of politics and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  concerns. In Asia ex Japan, Korea and India have received the largest inflows year-to-date according to Bloomberg.\par \par \uc2 While we expect capital inflows will continue to come in over the long run into both Asia and Indonesia, movements in the next one to two quarters are likely to be held hostage by increased \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth outlook.\par \par \uc2 We are concern over continued high government debt problems and deflation in the developed world in the second half of this year. Although we do not expect a double dip recession to occur, we believe that the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery will shift into a lower gear amid the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  pressure.\par \par \uc2 Another risk that could unfold is a US equity collapse. However, if US stocks can move sideways from current levels, as we expect, Asian markets including Indonesia should be able to outperform and move higher from current levels, which has broken through the 3,000 psychological barrier.\par \par \uc2 However, if equities in the developed markets (i.e. US and Europe) were to plunge, only bonds and cash would provide safe havens for investors. In this event, Asian markets including Indonesia would also plummet in our view.\par \par \uc2 Closer to home, investors' uneasiness over slowing global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is reflected in lower Indonesian market's daily turnover (Exhibit 1). July's average daily turnover has fallen to US$291 million, equal to the lowest 2010 monthly average daily trade back in February. This figure is also 18 percent lower than the 2009 daily average turnover of $353 million. With the World Cup fever out of the way, this persistently low daily average turnover is a source of concern at least in the short term.\par \par \uc2 Over the longer run, however, flows and Emerging Asia equities, including Indonesia will move higher due to three main reasons:\par \par \uc2 First, for well-known reasons, GDP growth will be established at a pace much faster than in the developed countries. Given low debt levels, both private and government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains well-placed to sustain solid growth even on withdrawn \b \highlight22\uc2 stimulus\b0 \highlight\uc2  measures like in China.\par \par \uc2 Second, \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  will move up to curb inflationary pressure and risk of overheating. This poses as a short-term challenge for local equities. Recently, the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has stated that they expect July's inflation to reach 1 percent, the highest this year.\par \par \uc2 However, as we expect Asian currencies to remain strong coupled with relatively muted commodity prices, we expect upcoming \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  tightening to be relatively mild (i.e. around 150bps for Indonesia in 2010-11, assuming inflation of 6 percent in 2010).\par \par \uc2 Therefore, we do not expect corporate earnings growth to experience major slowdowns. This is reflected in our basket of stocks with aggregate EPS growth for the market at 16.4 percent in 2010, remaining sustainable in 2011 at 16.5 percent year-on-year.\par \par \uc2 Finally, price-to-earnings ratios across the region remain reasonable, ranging around 10-20 times. The ratio for Indonesia is currently at 17.3 times for 2010, falling to 14.5 times in 2011, translating to next year's PEG of 0.9 times, still well below the maximum investable threshold of 1.2 times.\par \par \uc2 In summary, while short-term headwinds may slow capital inflows into the markets, medium-to-longer term equity prospects remain attractive.\par \par \uc2 The writer is the senior vice president and head of Indonesia research at Bahana Securities\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020100819e67m00046\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Pharmaceutical Importers to Have Two Import Identification Numbers;  \highlight22\uc2 Regulation \highlight\uc2  Revision Expected by August\b0\par\par\uc2 592 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 July 2010\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 Bisnis Indonesia    \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The Ministry of Trade is going to revise \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  45/M-DAG/PER/9/ 2009 on Import Identification Number (API) to make importers in the pharmaceutical sector to become producing as well as general importers.\par \par \uc2 Executive Director of the International Pharmaceutical Manufactures Group (IPMG) Parulian Simanjuntak revealed the importers had been summoned to the Coordinating Ministry for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs to discuss the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on API.\par \par \uc2 "We will issue it [API] to producing as well as general importers, but with some limits," he said yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Based on Minister of Trade \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  45/2009, API is an identification number that an importer has to have in importing goods.\par \par \uc2 API consists of general API (U) and producing API (P). API-U is given to importers that import goods for business by trading the goods to other parties.\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, API-P is given to importers that use the imported goods for their own production need. Article 5 of the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  reads that every importer is only allowed to have one API.\par \par \uc2 "After we express our objection to the requirements, we are contacted by the Minister of Trade. We asked them whether our proposal was accepted, but they only said it was positively responded," told Parulian.\par \par \uc2 One source at the Ministry of Trade confirmed the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be revised and issued earlier next month.\par \par \uc2 "Soon, the revised \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on API will be issued, but I don't know what the contents will be."\par \par \uc2 According to the source, the government only responded the businesses' objection.\par \par \uc2 He added when Permendag 45/2009 was issued on September 16, and would come into effect on January 1, 2011, some importers made outright rejection to it.\par \par \uc2 Parulian regretted the Ministry of Trade's lack of transparency in issuing policies. According to him, the government should be more transparent, so there would be no rejection to a \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 According to him, such an \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  had made drug and pharmaceutical raw material importers inefficient.\par \par \uc2 He took example that since the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on API was issued some importers had to import drugs at a larger volume to avoid the application of the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on January 1, 2011.\par \par \uc2 Parulian stated the Ministry had to decide on the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  revision by August this year since importers needed certainty for their import plans, which were scheduled three months in advance.\par \par \uc2 According to him, the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  could disrupt the procurement of several kinds of drugs that the people needed.\par \par \uc2 Parulian explained the government hinted importers could only import the goods for two years. After that, the imported goods should be able to be produced here.\par \par \uc2 He added only importers importing new goods or goods for samples and promotions that could hold both general and producing importers.\par \par \uc2 Parulian objected to the requirement since some products indeed could not yet be produced here due to limited technology and small demand, making the products inefficient to be produced on domestic level.\par \par \uc2 Certain products like bio-pharmaceutical and cancer drugs, he continued, could also not yet be produced by local manufacturers.\par \par \uc2 Has to choose\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, importers support a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of allowing importer to have only one import identification number (API).\par \par \uc2 Chairperson of the Indonesian National Importers Association (GINSI) Amiruddin Saud revealed importers should only be allowed to have one API, making them have to choose whether they wanted to become producing importer or general one.\par \par \uc2 "If one manufacturer wants to import goods to be sold, it should set up a new company." (Bisnis/sep)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020100729e67t00006\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 BI Rate flat, but stay watchful to inflation\b0\par\par\uc2 339 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 August 2010\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 Bisnis Indonesia    \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) Governor boards meeting (RDG) decided BI rate stays at the level of 6.50 percent or remains at the 13th steady position since August last year.\par \par \uc2 The decision was taken following a comprehensive evaluation to the latest development and \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospect in general which shows an ongoing progress.\par \par \uc2 However, Director of BI strategic planning and \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  relation Dyah N.K. Makhijani said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  also takes into account the inflation pressures recently by taking necessary monetary and banking policies.\par \par \uc2 "It aims to keep the inflation future progress on the right target of 5 percent or 1 percent by 2010 and 2011," she said in statement yesterday.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to maintain the BI rate at 6.50 percent is deemed adequate to keep the inflation expectation while staying watchful to the possible inflation rise.\par \par \uc2 In this light, BI in the near future will have some actions to tighten the liquidity control without disruption impact to banking intermediation, particularly through an adjustment of minimum reserve.\par \par \uc2 Besides, the governors boards recorded the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is still on the mounting trend with stable finance system.\par \par \uc2 This is seen from the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  progress in July 2010 which provides a recovery indication of domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  amidst the risk for global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  particularly dealing with the sluggish \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of China and US \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  prospect.\par \par \uc2 "\b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is predicted to have higher growth with the backup of the mounting export and investment performances with the robust consumption," he said.\par \par \uc2 In terms of offering, trade and industry sectors are assumingly growing up along with the mounting demand.\par \par \uc2 Senior economist of Bank Negara Indonesia Ryan Kiryanto considered BI decision to set a stagnant level of BI rate at 6.5 percent is right with the year on year inflation and year to date inflation under 5 percent.\par \par \uc2 He said the spread of the current inflation and BI rate is quite as big as 200 basis points so the lending rate is relatively stable. (Bisnis/hta/02)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020100805e6850000c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
