 \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: Indian companies are aggressively eyeing infrastructure projects in Indonesia, especially railways track projects to carry coal worth trillions of rupiah.\par \par \uc2 Earlier this week, \uc2 Reliance Power Ltd\uc2  announced they were ready to invest US$5 billion to develop coal railways track and coal mine in South Sumatra.\par \par \uc2 Moreover, India's PT \uc2 Adani Global\uc2  next year will work on the 270 kilometer long coal railways track in South Sumatra stretching from Tanjung Enim to Tanjung Carat (Tanjung Api-Api) worth US$1.6 billion.\par \par \uc2 The project is jointly developed by PT Bukit Asam Tbk, PT \uc2 Adani Global\uc2 , and the Provincial Government of South Sumatra.\par \par \uc2 "PT \uc2 Adani Global\uc2  will provide the financing, while Bukit Asam will supply 34 million tons in coal supply to be carried," said Head of the Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM) Gita Wirjawan during the signing of the head of agreement on the project yesterday.\par \par \uc2 The signing was attended by Minister of Transportation Freddy Numberi, Minister of Industry M.S. Hidayat and South Sumatra Governor Alex Noerdin.\par \par \uc2 President Director of PT \uc2 Adani Global\uc2  Ganeshan V. revealed for a start the Tanjung Enim-Tanjung Carat railways track would require US$1.65 billion, but it could grow bigger.\par \par \uc2 He explained the regional government controlled a 2% stake in the project, while Adani the rest 98%.\par \par \uc2 Information from the official website of Adani showed the Indian business group was a trading and infrastructure company established in 1988 and currently had branches in several countries, such as Indonesia, Singapore, Dubai, Mauritius, and Virginia.\par \par \uc2 Alex Noerdin confirmed there was no problem related to land acquisition since the project had been deliberated for three years. Besides, the three regencies that the railways track would pass, namely Muara Enim, Lahat, and Banyuasin, were committed to realizing the project.\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, Speaker of the Regional \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  of South Sumatra Wasista Bambang Utaya disclosed the partnership marked investors' confidence in the region.\par \par \uc2 Ganeshan said if the railways track in South Sumatra was successful, the company planned to develop some other railways tracks in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 "Indonesia is attractive to become a place to make infrastructure investments, especially outside Java."\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, PT Bukit Asam Tbk targets to produce 70 million tons of coal by 2016 following the completion of three coal railways tracks.\par \par \uc2 This year, the company targets to produce 12-13 million tons of coal and will increase it to 14 million tons next year.\par \par \uc2 President Director of PTBA Sukrisno explained the three railways tracks developed were Bukit Asam Transpacific Railway (BATR), \uc2 Adani Global\uc2 -owned railways track and railways track owned by state railways enterprise (PTKA).\par \par \uc2 "The railways track networks are supposed to be finished by 2014. However, to meet the maximum production and result, it will take around 2 years."\par \par \uc2 Operate in 2013\par \par \uc2 The \uc2 Adani Global\uc2 -owned railways track, said Gita, was expected to be finished next year and start full operation in 2013.\par \par \uc2 He explained the project was part of the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 -private partnership (PPP) projects.\par \par \uc2 "The current proper infrastructure development will attract long-term and added-value investments. It is such smart capital investments that Indonesia needs," he told.\par \par \uc2 The realization of the project could also accelerate the construction of an aluminum smelter worth US$3.2 billion made by a joint venture company established by the Provincial Government of South Sumatra and India's \uc2 National Aluminum Company Ltd\uc2  (Nalco).\par \par \uc2 The project, targeted to smelt 500,000 tons of aluminum per annum, has not been realized since 2008 due to coal supply \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Increasingly active\par \par \uc2 Record by Bisnis showed Indian energy companies over the past few years had been aggressively eyeing coal mines in Indonesia, including eyeing infrastructure networks developments.\par \par \uc2 This was attributable to the fact that India's rapid growing \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  bolstered its need for energy.\par \par \uc2 Reliance Power Ltd\uc2 , for example, is building a power plant with a capacity of 35,000 megawatt in India.\par \par \uc2 Therefore, Vice President Boediono asked CEO of \uc2 Reliance Power Ltd\uc2  Jayarama Prasad Chalasani to make the company work on electricity projects in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Gita said the BKPM would review the aspiration of the Indian company.\par \par \uc2 He added investors were also asked to coordinate with the related regional governments since the projects would directly be related to the people's needs. (Bisnis/zuf/06/mcd/bpj)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020100826e68q00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
