\par\par \b \uc2 Foreign funds continue to flow into local stock market\b0\par\par\uc2 512 \uc2 words\par \uc2 20 September 2010\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 Foreign funds continue to dominate trading on the Indonesian Stock Exchange (IDX) as global fund managers move into emerging markets for higher returns, a securities analyst said.\par \par \uc2 The surge in foreign capital sent the benchmark Jakarta composite index (JCI) to a new record high last week. After a five-day break ending Tuesday, the JCI climbed 154 points, or almost 5 percent, from Wednesday to Friday, to close at an all-time high of 3,384.\par \par \uc2 The IDX data showed over Rp 3 trillion (US$333 million) of net foreign purchases were booked during the three-day rally, during which total transactions surpassed Rp 18 trillion. The total amount of capital inflow has surpassed Rp 19 trillion so far this year.\par \par \uc2 Foreign investors have been pouring capital in Southeast Asia's biggest \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , due to strong \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals and corporate earnings, which have performed strongly this year.\par \par \uc2 Securities analysts, however, warned that \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in some European countries and the slow \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in the US, should be closely watched, saying that another crash in the capital market could occur in the future if the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  does not improve.\par \par \uc2 "If there's a shock in the global market, it could lead to rapid outflow of foreign funds from the local exchange," said Fauzi Ichsan, a senior economist at Standard Chartered \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "Foreign investors have shifted their idle funds from the money market to the stock market due to more promising gains," said Yanuar Rizky, a stock market analyst.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia, according to Fauzi, benefits from the foreign splurge as the JCI continues to make gains among other regional indexes.\par \par \uc2 The JCI is one of Asia's best-performing indexes, gaining over 31 percent so far this year, compared to other Asian peers like Singapore's Strait Times Index, which has advanced 6.2 percent, Hong Kong's Hang Seng Index 0.67 percent gain and Tokyo's Nikkei 9.6 percent loss.\par \par \uc2 Mandiri Sekuritas chief economist, Destry Damayanti, said that strong expectations for corporate earnings had further fueled investors' enthusiasm to invest in the country.\par \par \uc2 "Third quarter financial results will come up soon, and so far, companies in the country have shown excellent earnings growth," she said, citing dividend payout as another additional push factor for investors to invest in stocks.\par \par \uc2 Fuad Rahmany, head of the Capital Market and Financial Institutions Supervisory Agency (Bapepam-LK), had warned that the surge in foreign funds could lead to large capital outflow, which would then result in the collapse of share prices in the local exchange.\par \par \uc2 "I ask local investors to not get emotional. Don't just follow foreign investors' moves," Fuad said, as quoted by business magazine Kontan.\par \par \uc2 The Asian Development Bank and the International Monetary Fund have also warned against capital flows to Asian countries including Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Surges in capital flows may also lead to asset bubbles and increase systemic risks for the financial\par \par \uc2 system, in addition to exchange rate fluctuations and surges in inflation, the financial agencies warned. (est)\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020100920e69k00010\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 BNI's Rights Issue Portion to Decrease; Index Potential to Hit 3,500\b0\par\par\uc2 1,064 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 September 2010\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The portion of \uc2 PT Bank Negara Indonesia Tbk\uc2 's (BNI) rights issue decreases from 18.1% to 14.54% since the management stock option program (MSOP) will come from the scheme.\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, \uc2 PT Bank Mandiri Tbk\uc2  will be ready if the shareholders ask the company to do its rights issue next year despite the current stellar market performance, showed by an increase of 2.07% or 70.41 points in the Composite Stock Index (IHSG) yesterday to 3,468.04.\par \par \uc2 Chairperson of the House Commission VI Airlangga Hartarto revealed the House asked the government to maintain its share of 60% in BNI, making the management stock option program (MSOP) to be included in the rights issue of 18.1% shares.\par \par \uc2 "The portion of new shares to be issued by BNI will decrease to 14.54% from 18.1% due to the MSOP, which involves a 3.56% stake," he told after a working meeting with the State Minister for State-owned Enterprises (SOEs) discussing the rights issues of \uc2 Bank BNI\uc2  and Mandiri yesterday.\par \par \uc2 According to the plan, BNI will issue 3.374 billion shares or 18.10% to bolster \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  shares to 40% or 7.459 billion shares from the outstanding shares of 18.65 billion shares.\par \par \uc2 However, the figure has not yet put into account 664.08 million shares or 3.56% shares for the MSOP. The House finally asks the MSOP to be included in the rights issue, but the exercise should be separated from the corporate action, making BNI unable to directly enjoy \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  discount on \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  shares as the amount of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  shares is less than 40%. "BNI cannot directly enjoy \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  discount on \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  shares."\par \par \uc2 Based on Government \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  (PP) 81 year 2007 on Income \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a company can have a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  discount of 5% if its \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  shares amount to at least 40%.\par \par \uc2 One BNI executive who prefers anonymity disclosed if the MSOP was included in the rights issue and the exercise was conducted separately, this will make BNI share price slump."\par \par \uc2 It was because, he added, investors buying new BNI shares would want to enjoy gain from dividends paid from the 2010 financial performance, assuming the rights issue realized in November this year.\par \par \uc2 Mandiri to accept\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2  will be ready to accept the possibility of having its rights issue not to be realized this year.\par \par \uc2 President Director of Bank Mandiri Zulkifli Zaini said the state lender was waiting for the State Minister for SOEs' decision on the rights issue schedule.\par \par \uc2 "We hope the rights issue can be realized as scheduled. However, whether it is BNI or Mandiri that will first realize the rights issue will depend on the State Minister for SOEs. So, we will accept any decision made by the Ministry."\par \par \uc2 The rights issue schedules for BNI and Mandiri are again \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  since the meeting between the House Commission VI and Commission XI leaves the schedule arrangement to the State Ministry for SOEs, while according to the plan BNI and Mandiri will hold the rights issue by November and December 2010, respectively.\par \par \uc2 "As for the schedules, the government will arrange them based on the readiness of each SOE in a bid to create optimal privatization," said State Minister for SOEs Mustafa Abubakar.\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, Minister of Finance \uc2 Agus Martowardojo\uc2  as the state asset manager representative suggested the right issue schedules not to be announced to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  first. "Such an announcement will affect the market."\par \par \uc2 When asked about the possibility of the government absorbing the rights issue, Agus denied it. "The government has no \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to absorb the new shares of the two banks."\par \par \uc2 Under the post-rights issue schemes, BNI is expected to find its profit rising 29.3% and \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2  27.21% in the next four years. Moreover, BNI and Mandiri are projected to have their dividend contributions increasing by 27.21% and 23.66%, respectively.\par \par \uc2 Amid the rights issue of the two state lenders, the Composite Stock Index (IHSG) again hit a new record high of 3,468.04. Some market players even forecasted the index to soon hit 3,575.\par \par \uc2 Last week, the IHSG hit a new record high of 3,397.63, with foreign net buy reaching IDR800 billion in that week.\par \par \uc2 Foreign fund flow\par \par \uc2 The flow of foreign funds to the domestic capital market is viewed to trigger the bourse rally. Yesterday, foreign investors booked IDR1.72 trillion in purchase, with total net buy reaching IDR85.57 billion.\par \par \uc2 Head of Research at PT Universal Broker Indonesia Satrio Utomo revealed foreign investors might continue to be interested in injecting funds to the Indonesian bourse for the next two years, thanks to the strong \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  positive sentiments and national finance.\par \par \uc2 "Amid Indonesia's positive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition, Indonesia's rating may be upgraded to investment grade in 2011 or 2012. Only after three year the bourse will worry about political change following the general election," he told Bisnis yesterday.\par \par \uc2 In the short-term, he added, the IHSG might touch 3,500-3,575 as long as regional bourses could support the IHSG rally.\par \par \uc2 Yesterday, the IHSG rally was supported by increases in the prices of 166 shares. The really took place at the same time with the rallies on some major Asian bourses, such as Hang Seng (1%), Nikkei 225 (1.39%), and KOSPI (0.77%).\par \par \uc2 "If the foreign fund inflow is still strong, there is no reason to deny that the IHSG probably will hit 3,950. This is the same when we last year said a level of 3,200 would not be achieved this year," said Satrio.\par \par \uc2 Besides, the market cap had also been increasing following the rights issue plan and the IPOs of some big publicly listed companies, especially SOEs.\par \par \uc2 Separately, an analyst at PT Panin Sekuritas Tbk Purwoko Sartono viewed the blue-chip stock rallies yesterday would be potential to lead the index to hit a new record high today.\par \par \uc2 "We view the index still has an opportunity to test the resistance level at 3,500. Banking and consumer goods sector stocks are still attractive choices for transactions," he said.\par \par \uc2 Positive sentiments on the bourse, he added, were created by expectation for low inflation and bright \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth outlook. (Bisnis/ags/hta/02/05/09/iaa)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020100928e69s00001\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
