\par\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  risks losing momentum: Experts\b0\par\par\uc2 513 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 November 2010\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 The Jakarta Post    \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 The Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has never looked better, with significant improvements in key areas, but economists and business players have warned of flaws that could deter investors.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia's gross domestic product is expected to grow by more than 6 percent this year, up from 4.5 percent in 2009, fueled by higher exports, increased investment and strong consumer \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Inflation is contained, stock prices are at record levels, and the rupiah has also strengthened.\par \par \uc2 Capital is also flowing in in large quantities, both for portfolio and physical investment, as Indonesia maintains \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political stability.\par \par \uc2 Most rating agencies have ranked Indonesia a notch or two below investment grade, which means it is at a low risk of defaulting. Several Japanese rating agencies have already given Indonesia the top rating.\par \par \uc2 However, as with most good news there is also the "but".\par \par \uc2 In a discussion on the prospect of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , organized by the Jakarta Foreign Correspondents Club on Thursday, economists and a businessman warned about the poor implementation of many of the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  plans, in particular the desperate shortage of infrastructure including roads, ports and power plants.\par \par \uc2 "Infrastructure is our biggest bottleneck," said Sofjan Wanandi, the chairman of the Indonesian Employers Association and the owner/founder of the Gemala business group.\par \par \uc2 The government is lagging in its plan to improve Indonesia's power supply capacity, casting \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the viability of some of the investment projects in the country.\par \par \uc2 The government, Sofjan said, needs to do its homework to translate the rising interest among foreign investors into actual physical investment, and not simply limit it to portfolio investment in Indonesian stocks and bonds.\par \par \uc2 "We have to start implementing or else we will lose the momentum," Sofjan said.\par \par \uc2 Recognizing that some investment had been taking place in Indonesia in recent years, he noted that most investors concentrated on extraction industries, services, property and automotive, and very little in labor-intensive manufacturing sectors.\par \par \uc2 Bank Danamon chief economist Anton Gunawan noted \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  inconsistencies, such in the setting of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's key interest rate that did not support the national inflation target.\par \par \uc2 He also said the government's pledge to improve inter-connectivity in Indonesia did not correspond to its decision to prioritize road transportation rather than inter-island transportation.\par \par \uc2 While both the official unemployment rate and poverty figures have declined, Anton said, they both remained high in absolute figures. He added that unemployment had declined largely because more people had been employed in the informal sector.\par \par \uc2 Anton cautioned that the capital inflows into Indonesia's stocks and bond markets could carry risks of sudden reversals.\par \par \uc2 Frederica Widyasari Dewi, the director of development at the Indonesian Stock Exchange, said two-thirds of the market capitalization was in the form of foreign funds. The agency is currently conducting a promotional campaign in the region, since only around 1 percent of the Indonesian population have stock investments at present.\par \par \uc2 Other speakers at the discussion were Finance Ministry advisor Edward Gustely and \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2  economist Moch. Doddy Ariefianto.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020101105e6b50001i\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw177\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2655\pichgoal600
