\par\par \b \uc2 RI on track to get investment grade\b0\par\par\uc2 551 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 November 2010\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 14\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 The Jakarta Post    \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 Indonesia's debt is well on track to achieve an investment grade in line with the continued improvement of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, a senior \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  official has said.\par \par \uc2 Perry Warjiyo, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's director of monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  research, said the world's major\par \par \uc2 rating agencies had continued to positively rate Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance.\par \par \uc2 Perry said that based on the statements made by several rating agencies during a recent meeting, "we are optimistic that we will get the rating upgrade to investment grade next year".\par \par \uc2 He added that in the meetings, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  convinced the agencies that the country's macroeconomy was stable and that the debt-to-GDP (growth domestic product) ratio was lowering.\par \par \uc2 In the 2011 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  recently approved by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the debt ratio against the GDP was set at 26 percent, or lower than this year's 27.4 percent.\par \par \uc2 In 2009, the ratio stood at 30 percent and it reached 54 percent in 2004.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has grown in the 4-6 percent range in recent years and is expected to expand by 6.3 percent in 2011.\par \par \uc2 The government has also forecast the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to grow up to 7.7 percent by the end of President\par \par \uc2 Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono's tenure in 2014.\par \par \uc2 The world's three major rating agencies -- \uc2 Moody's\uc2  Investors Services, \uc2 Standard & Poor's\uc2  (S&P) and Fitch Ratings -- have upgraded Indonesia's sovereign debt rating this year to one and two notches below investment grade.\par \par \uc2 "Rating agencies continue to upgrade their ratings and they all have given positive outlook," Perry told reporters in Jakarta on Friday.\par \par \uc2 In January, Fitch upgraded Indonesia's long-term foreign and local-currency credit ratings to BB+ with stable outlook, or one level below investment grade -- the highest since the 1997 Asian financial crisis.\par \par \uc2 In March, two months after the Fitch upgrade, S&P raised Indonesia's sovereign debt rating to the highest level in 12 years to BB with positive outlook, or two levels below investment grade.\par \par \uc2 "Investment grade" is awarded when government bonds are considered stable enough for banks to invest in.\par \par \uc2 In June of this year, \uc2 Moody's\uc2  raised Indonesia's credit rating to "positive" from the previous "stable" after upgrading the country's debt rating to two levels below investment grade in September 2009.\par \par \uc2 Perry added that from the meetings the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  went through with rating agencies, it was noted that the country's investment climate needed a boost.\par \par \uc2 "Infrastructure and legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  are also keys to the success of obtaining investment grade."\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Perry added, has told the agencies that "we are doing all that we can do but we need time to solve the problems".\par \par \uc2 "Other indicators are far better than other countries with investment grade. So our issues should not hamper the rating upgrade.\par \par \uc2 Japan Credit Rating Agency was the first to raise Indonesia's sovereign debt rating to investment grade when in July, it upgraded the country's foreign currency rating by a notch to BBB-.\par \par \uc2 The Japanese rating agency said the country could "sustain modest \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth while maintaining macroeconomic stability and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  soundness in the years to come". (est)\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020101108e6b80001f\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 'Revision of Cabotage Creates Legal  \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty \highlight\uc2 '\b0\par\par\uc2 408 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 November 2010\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 Bisnis Indonesia    \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The revision of Law 17 year 2008 on Shipping that regulates the cabotage principle is viewed to create legal and business \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in Indonesia despite the fact that some offshore boats indeed have not been made available in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 A maritime lecturer at the Surabaya November 10th Institute of Technology Saut Gurning argued it was unnecessary to revise the Shipping Law at the moment since the national shipping industry believed they would be able to provide national offshore boats if they were given the chance.\par \par \uc2 According to him, the government's plan to revise the two-year Shipping Law would instead create a perception that there was no business and legal certainty in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 "The cost will be bigger," he told Bisnis yesterday.\par \par \uc2 He suggested the government focused on improving the licensing process for foreign boats operating in Indonesia to become Indonesia-flagged ones.\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, Secretary of the Care for Shipping, Port, and Maritime Environment Society (Mappel) Maman Permana said drilling ship, jack up rig, MODU, 2D seismic, 3D seismic, and construction could be categorized as non-boats.\par \par \uc2 However, he said, it would not need to revise the Shipping Law to accommodate such oil and gas offshore equipment. "We don't need to revise the Shipping Law. The most important thing is we have to put the application of the cabotage principle on the track."\par \par \uc2 Various parties have urged the government to stop its efforts to revise Law No.17 year 2008 on Shipping, which regulates the cabotage principle (a principle that requires domestic commodities to be carried by Indonesia-flagged boats).\par \par \uc2 They view that the current 9,700 Indonesia-flagged boats have been able to serve nearly all domestic passenger and cargo transportation activities.\par \par \uc2 A member of the House Commission V Abdul Hakim said the shipping businesses indeed had not been able to procure boats of some categories, but they had been able to cater to nearly all domestic transportation needs.\par \par \uc2 The government is thinking of revising the cabotage principle since the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  is considered potential to curb offshore oil and gas exploration activities, which in turn will curb the fulfillment of oil lifting and state revenues targets.\par \par \uc2 Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Hatta Rajasa said there were some types of foreign boats that the Indonesian shipping businesses could not yet procure. Among the types are drilling ship, jack up rig, 3D seismic, and construction equipment. (Bisnis/aji)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020101108e6b80002z\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
