\par\par \b \uc2 Reflections on topsy-turvy process of doing business\b0\par\par\uc2 1,009 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 November 2010\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 7\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Kumba Digdowiseiso, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 Of all the key factors hampering \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in Indonesia, one of the most commonly cited is the low-level of new domestic and foreign investment. Although there are many factors that contribute to investment, all firms are essentially facing difficulty obtaining business permits and licenses.\par \par \uc2 In the World Bank's 2011 Doing Business survey of 183 countries, Indonesia's position decreased from 115th to 121st, making the country's overall business performance just slightly higher than other ASEAN countries such as Cambodia, Laos, and the Philippines.\par \par \uc2 Also, of the nine indicators in the Doing Business survey, the variable of starting a business in Indonesia improved significantly. However, we performed poorly in protecting investors, paying \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , getting credit, registering property, enforcing contracts, closing a business, and trading across borders, with no significant change in construction permits.\par \par \uc2 I personally believe that those results are not surprising at all as there has been no continuous improvement in terms of regulations as well as bureaucratic reform as far as obtaining licenses goes.\par \par \uc2 Pertaining to the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  issue, now that decentralization has come into effect, the regional governments should create a conducive business climate to attract investment into their regions.\par \par \uc2 However, their privilege of making regional regulations has often hampered investment because they are more concerned with increasing local revenue through levies.\par \par \uc2 In general, there are four principles for assessing the appropriateness of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  at the regional level, such as the sufficiency of yield, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  efficiency, equity, the capacity of implementation, and the compatibility of \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the regional source of income (Devas et al, 1989).\par \par \uc2 With respect to the regional governments' \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  capacity, their \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue could come from various sources, including \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  sharing with the central government, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  levied by the regional government themselves and additional \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  levied from the central government \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Ironically, the discretion in taxing has increased their creativity in designing other forms of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and various kinds of new retributions in a bid to avoid the limit of the existing \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The Regional Autonomy Watch's survey (2009) confirmed the existence of levies that have the potential to cause a high-cost \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the investment climate, including those with improper and different \b \highlight22\uc2 tariff\b0 \highlight\uc2  structures, levies that double-up with those at the central and provincial levels, or even those that overlap with other similar levies imposed by other regulations from the same municipal government, are common in some regions.\par \par \uc2 For example, Ordinance of the Trade Ministry No. 36/2007 on the Issuance of Trading Licenses, states that there is no fee for making a new trading license (SIUP). Similarly, administration fee for a new company registration (TDP) simply does not exist according to Ordinance of the Trade Ministry No. 37/2007 on Company Registration. Yet, no businesspeople in regional areas enjoy new SIUP and TDP free of charge.\par \par \uc2 On top of regulatory issues, there are also bureaucratic challenges in implementing business licenses. According to The Asia Foundation (2008), the actual implementation of business licenses often suffers from a lack of government capacity and resources, which prevents the government from providing social protection, market control, or information collection.\par \par \uc2 In principle, the central government through the Home Ministry has developed a One Stop Shop (OSS) licensing service center to improve the quality of bureaucratic reform. This manifests itself in a Single Window Integrated Service (PTSP) at the regional level for the purpose of business licensing.\par \par \uc2 This idea is similar to those in other ASEAN countries, such as Thailand's One Start-One Stop Investment Center, Singapore's Online Business Licensing Service, and Malaysia's Business Licensing Electronic Support System.\par \par \uc2 Unlike those countries, the Home Ministry's PTSP in some areas does not play a big role in licensing activity. Ideally, all permits such as permits for building, trade and industry, would all be processed in this body.\par \par \uc2 But, most of these permits are not performed there since there is no willingness from the local elites to speed up business licensing activities in PTSP. This, in turn, affects the time and cost that businessmen spend.\par \par \uc2 Take the example of provincial government of Jakarta that just launched a one-stop investment service.\par \par \uc2 While this sounds promising for investors, it shows a lack of commitment by the governor to socialize PTSP as this body was actually established in 2007.\par \par \uc2 Also, he did not commit to force regional government representatives (e.g. regional revenue office and regional trade office) associated with the issuance of the permits to be placed at the PTSP office.\par \par \uc2 From the two above issues, it is clear that the problem in cost, the precision of time, and procedure in business license is still a major hindrance for many investors. For those who want to expedite the business process or even ensure the approval of a possibly inadequate application, these drive them to pay more. In this case, bribery may not only be initiated by government officials, but also by businessmen who try to find a short-cut in the process.\par \par \uc2 Now, we are hoping for an improved license system in the PTSP. President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono launched an ambitious plan of utilizing investment to increase GDP growth for Southeast Asia's biggest \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from 6.3 percent in 2011 to 7.7 percent in 2014.\par \par \uc2 Therefore, setting a national standard that has flexibility with regional capacity will aid this process. On \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the need to change \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives to the revenue sharing mechanism is essential for mitigating the practice of using regional regulations to simply increase regional revenues as this can have a positive effect on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 Last, all of these solutions would not be possible to improve the business licensing regime in Indonesia unless there is an inter-ministerial consensus as well as leadership from the presidential and local elites to realize the benefits.\par \par \uc2 The writer, an alumnus in Applied Economics at The University of Adelaide, Australia, is a lecturer at National University, Jakarta, and an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  researcher at Transparency International Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020101123e6bn0003j\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Vice President:  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  to be Accelerated Next Year\b0\par\par\uc2 525 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 November 2010\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: The government is optimistic to accelerate development starting next year as a first step to meet the medium-term target to have an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 7%-8%, with eyes still are on post-global crisis risks.\par \par \uc2 Vice President Boediono said Indonesia had a good capital to bolster its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth figure this year had been followed by programs that directly touched upon the aspect of the people's welfare.\par \par \uc2 "If we can improve this, Indonesia will be in a strong position to face challenges ahead. I am optimistic that we have good capitals to accelerate our development," he said when receiving the visit of Publisher of Bisnis Indonesia daily Sukamdani Sahid Gitosardjono in the Vice Presidential Office yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Also present at the meeting were Lulu Terianto (President Director of PT Jurnalindo Aksara Grafika, the publisher of Bisnis Indonesia), Ahmad Djauhar (Director of JAG and Deputy Publisher of Bisnis Indonesia), and Arief Budisusilo (Editor-in-Chief of Bisnis Indonesia), and the editorial staff. The meeting is part of the 25th anniversary of Bisnis Indonesia on December 14, 2010.\par \par \uc2 Boediono continued Indonesia ahead would be able to match China and India. The Vice President was optimistic Indonesia would be able to meet an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 7%-8% in the medium- and long-term. Indonesia had proved for nearly 30 years that its \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could grow by more than 7%.\par \par \uc2 The key, he added, was every element of the nation should run its function well. The government, the business industry, politicians, and media had to run their respective function and role within the same corridor, namely the interests of the nation of Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 "Opinion difference is natural, but we have to remember that we are living in one big corporation called Indonesia that we have to preserve together."\par \par \uc2 However, he reminded that the major challenges to Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead were not domestic problems, but the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions. According to him, many developed countries had not been able to make adjustments due to the aftermath of the global crisis.\par \par \uc2 So far, added Boediono, the issue of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  imbalance had not been settled. No strict adjustment had taken place among developed countries, precisely like the condition that we saw happening in Europe at the moment.\par \par \uc2 Several developed countries were still experiencing the confidence crisis in surviving the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development due to the impacts of the 2008 crisis.\par \par \uc2 "We can withstand crisis with good confidence. This is a good capital for Indonesia ahead."\par \par \uc2 Separately, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) Governor Darmin Nasution said the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the government had taken various measures in maintaining macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability.\par \par \uc2 "This is an important precondition to achieve sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth," he stated in his written welcome speech at the Market Outlook 2011 seminar yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Objective coverage\par \par \uc2 In the meantime, the Vice President asked the media to make objective coverage based on facts and avoid sensational coverage.\par \par \uc2 He warned that sensational news or coverage would only give a temporary gain of increasing newspaper circulation. In the long run, however, it would injure the media itself. (Bisnis/asd)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020101126e6bq00002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
