\par\par \b \uc2 Wiratman Wangsadinata: Tireless soul in quest of a better Indonesia\b0\par\par\uc2 Ika Krismantari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta    \par \uc2 906 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 December 2010\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 32\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 The Jakarta Post    \par \par \uc2 JP/R.BERTO WEDHATAMABeing 75 hasn't stopped Indonesia's top engineer, Wiratman Wangsadinata, from achieving wonders.\par \par \uc2 While most of his peers spend leisurely time at home in their later years, Wiratman is still busy working 9 to 5, Monday to Friday at his office on Jl. T.B. Simatupang, South Jakarta.\par \par \uc2 "This is how I enjoy my old age. I like it this way rather than doing nothing that in the end would\par \par \uc2 make me sick," Wiratman told The Jakarta Post in a recent interview at his office.\par \par \uc2 Situated in a humble meeting room, the Post had the chance to steal Wiratman away from his work to do a one-hour interview last week.\par \par \uc2 Wearing simple brown batik, the energetic elderly man started the interview by sharing a story about his enduring love for the construction world.\par \par \uc2 "It started because construction was Indonesia's spearhead for development. \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development would not work without support from the construction and infrastructure sector ... Therefore, I wanted to participate in making this development work," the man said of the main reason he got into the engineering world.\par \par \uc2 With strong determination, Wiratman took a major in civil engineering at the Bandung Institute of Technology (ITB) in 1954.\par \par \uc2 And he has never looked back.\par \par \uc2 He has been involved in numerous infrastructure projects in Indonesia. His brilliant ideas and innovation have given birth to many spectacular structural designs in the country.\par \par \uc2 These include the Muria Nuclear Power Plant in Central Java, the Mass Rapid Transportation project in Jakarta and the upcoming Sunda Strait Bridge, which is an ambitious government plan to connect Java and Sumatra.\par \par \uc2 No wonder people refer to Wiratman as the great mind behind all of Indonesia's controversial infrastructure projects.\par \par \uc2 Another remarkable thing about Wiratman is his integrity and unwavering commitment to his\par \par \uc2 profession.\par \par \uc2 Despite his close relations with a number of top government officials, Wiratman has always shied away from taking advantage of his personal network for his office projects.\par \par \uc2 Former president B.J. Habibie is a high school friend of Wiratman, but his company, Wiratman and Associates, has never accepted projects from his close pal.\par \par \uc2 "In the office, I always direct my employees to avoid unethical practices," Wiratman said.\par \par \uc2 He has also shown the same principle in the latest project, the Sunda Strait Bridge.\par \par \uc2 The head of the national team for the project, Hermanto Dardak, admires Wiratman for his integrity.\par \par \uc2 "He rejected the idea of being appointed the head of the advisory board for the government because of his company's position as the designer in the project," Herman, who is also the deputy \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  works minister, said recently.\par \par \uc2 But apart from his integrity, the father of two also admits to being a "master thief".\par \par \uc2 The rapid progress in the global construction sector, for him, has required Indonesian engineers to "steal" knowledge from their international counterparts to stay knowledgeable about the latest technology.\par \par \uc2 "The greatest challenge is learning about the technological developments out there because they can no longer be found in textbooks. If we don't stay up-to-date, we will end up the fools and lose the competition," he said.\par \par \uc2 For the Sunda Strait Bridge, Wiratman said he went to Italy to observe the similar Messina Bridge project and meet engineers and researchers involved in the project.\par \par \uc2 Wiratman also has a strong sense of nationalism and believes Indonesian engineers have the same capabilities as their foreign counterparts.\par \par \uc2 He himself has proven that by discovering new formulas and systems, which have been applied in engineering elsewhere.\par \par \uc2 Now more than 50 years have passed since Wiratman fell in love with engineering, but amazingly we still can see the same spirit and strong integrity and continuous hard work despite his advanced age.\par \par \uc2 To celebrate his 50 years in engineering, Wiratman recently published a book titled Momentum and Innovation 1960 - 2010.\par \par \uc2 The book displays various monumental infrastructure projects by Wiratman, including the Borobudur restoration, which strengthened his label as an expert in quake-resistant buildings in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Behind his indisputable reputation as an engineer, Wiratman is a great family man.\par \par \uc2 Happily married for more than 50 years to Rohani, Wiratman now has four grandchildren and likes to spend weekends with the whole family.\par \par \uc2 "There will always be a time for my family," the man, who enjoys reading, singing and painting, said.\par \par \uc2 To stay fit, Wiratman said he takes a one-hour morning walk around his neighborhood every day.\par \par \uc2 "I used to like playing badminton or go swimming. But now that I am no longer able, I just go for a walk every day," Wiratman said with a hint of a Sundanese accent.\par \par \uc2 But living for Wiratman is still working and creating something and never stopping.\par \par \uc2 Therefore, despite his advanced age, he never tires of finding ways to improve the local engineering sector and dealing with challenges that apparently come from the government.\par \par \uc2 "I don't think the support from the government is real in contributing to the improvement of engineering expertise," he said, referring to unfair remuneration systems for foreign and local engineers, corrupt construction schemes that have brought some projects to a halt and of course the government's slow reaction and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in many projects.\par \par \uc2 "I hope my book will give people the spirit to fight the unjust system. By working professionally, I believe we can move forward," he said.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020101203e6c30001k\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
