\par\par \b \uc2 BI keeps rate, mulls new  \highlight22\uc2 policy \highlight\uc2  to tame inflation\b0\par\par\uc2 562 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 December 2010\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) decided Friday to maintain its benchmark rate at a record-low of 6.5 percent for the 16th month despite worries that the surge in the capital inflow would further fuel rising inflationary pressure.\par \par \uc2 BI spokesman Difi Johansyah said Friday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's board of directors agreed during the monthly \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  meeting to retain the benchmark rate at the current level because raising the rate would attract more foreign funds into Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  was still preparing a non-interest rate instrument to ease the inflationary pressure partly resulting from the inflow of foreign capital into the country, he said.\par \par \uc2 "The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will include managing foreigners' funds in vostro accounts [current rupiah accounts held by non-residents in local banks], as well as raising the foreign currency minimum reserve requirement (GWM) that banks must store at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he told reporters at BI.\par \par \uc2 BI is also currently preparing a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  that will require banks to increase their foreign currency-based reserve requirement, although details, especially related to the percentage of the increase, have yet to be revealed.\par \par \uc2 However, BI director for monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  research Perry Warjiyo has hinted that rates will likely be raised back to levels before the 2008 crisis, when BI lowered the amount of foreign currency \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  that banks must store at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  from three percent to one percent of a bank's total third party funds.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  recently raised banks' rupiah reserve requirement to 8 percent of their deposits to keep inflation in check, up from 5 percent previously.\par \par \uc2 The measure enabled the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to reduce money in circulation to about Rp 50 trillion (about US$5.6 billion).\par \par \uc2 The increase in the reserve requirement has enabled the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to effectively vent inflationary pressures. This measure enabled the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to keep its benchmark rate at a record low 6.5 percent for a 16th straight month.\par \par \uc2 Central banks in other Asian countries recently raised their \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to curb the inflation.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  viewed the rising inflation rate as manageable, partly in thanks to a stronger rupiah, Difi said.\par \par \uc2 "External inflationary pressures, which are partly due to soaring international commodity prices ... could be compensated by the appreciation trend of the rupiah exchange rate," he said in a statement released Friday.\par \par \uc2 The rupiah has so far appreciated by about five percent this year to the range of Rp 9,000 against the US dollar, making it one of Asia's best performing currencies. The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has said that it intervened in the rupiah to prevent aggressive advancement that could hurt exports and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 The Central Statistics Agency (BPS) announced Wednesday a relatively high monthly inflation rate of 0.6 percent in November, bringing total calendar year (January-November) inflation to 5.98 percent, just beneath the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's high-end target of 6 percent for full year 2010.\par \par \uc2 "With the latest figures, the consumer prices index's inflation may slightly surpass our initial target by the end of 2010," Difi added.\par \par \uc2 Despite the so-called "quite high" inflation rate in November, Difi said the pressures mainly came from volatile food prices, which are \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  by nature, while core inflation remained manageable at 4.31 percent in November. (est)\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020101204e6c40001d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
