on was expected to be stronger, leading to higher \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth than this year.\par \par \uc2 Next year, Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is estimated at 6.2%, not yet to reach 7% projected by the government.\par \par \uc2 The World Bank is of an opinion that Indonesia had to make investments in critical infrastructures and in job-creating \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities to be able to meet an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target of 7%.\par \par \uc2 "The recently approved 2011 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is a positive measure since it increases capital \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  and contains additional measures to deal with barriers related to slow \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  disbursement."\par \par \uc2 Optimistic\par \par \uc2 Separately, State Minister/Head of the Bappenas Armida Alisjahbana was optimistic Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the fourth quarter of 2010 would increase from 5.8% recorded in the third quarter.\par \par \uc2 "We hope the Q4 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth can be higher than the Q3 one. I hope the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  can grow by 6.1%," she said yesterday.\par \par \uc2 Such a confidence, added Armida, was based on stronger consumptions, better exports, and higher investments. Moreover, the role of government \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  would also surge in the last quarter.\par \par \uc2 Deputy Minister of Agriculture Bayu Krisnamurthi added weather \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  was predicted to affect food prices. (Bisnis/agi/14)\par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020101217e6ch00003\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
