\par\par \b \uc2 Fauzi pats himself on back for 2010 progress\b0\par\par\uc2 529 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 December 2010\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 5\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2010 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 In his year-end statement Wednesday, Jakarta Governor Fauzi Bowo claimed success in tackling Jakarta's multifaceted problems.\par \par \uc2 Fauzi said that throughout 2010, his administration had attained success in implementing its programs and improving the welfare of\par \par \uc2 Jakartans.\par \par \uc2 Fauzi said the increased prosperity of Jakartans was evident in the positive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth that the city enjoyed this year.\par \par \uc2 "In the first quarter of 2010, we saw 6.2 percent growth and it increased steadily until the end of the year," Fauzi said in a press briefing.\par \par \uc2 Data from the city administration put \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in Jakarta at 6.7 percent in the second quarter and 6.5 percent in the third quarter. It is expected to flat-line until early next year.\par \par \uc2 Fauzi attributed the growth to consumption, which contributed more than 55 percent to the city \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In 2010, the service and manufacturing sectors also grew significantly at 71 percent and 28.2 percent respectively.\par \par \uc2 Fauzi said the decreased poverty rate and the increase in the number of school graduates were indicators of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  progress.\par \par \uc2 "We've seen a steady decline in the poverty rate since 2007," he said.\par \par \uc2 He quoted figures from the Central Statistics Agency (BPS), which reveal that the number of people living below the poverty line currently stood at 312,000, down from 323,000 last year. The figure stood at 405,000 in 2007 and 379,000 in 2008.\par \par \uc2 This year, Jakarta also saw an increased number of school graduates.\par \par \uc2 "This year, 99.5 percent of students graduated from elementary, junior and high schools," he said.\par \par \uc2 Fauzi said that the improvement in education was partly due to funds earmarked from the city \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . "We have allocated 28.18 percent of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for education, equalling Rp 7.39 trillion (US$820.29 million)."\par \par \uc2 Despite major flooding throughout the year and worsening traffic problems, Fauzi claimed that he was able to put them in check.\par \par \uc2 "The busway lane clearance has had a positive result. We now have faster traveling times, a 26 percent increase in the number of people traveling on the busway and a 56 percent decline in busway-related accidents," he said.\par \par \uc2 Fauzi also said that a better solution to Jakarta's traffic woes was on its way. He said the construction of the a Mass Rapid Transit system connecting Lebak Bulus and Dukuh Atas would soon start, with the land clearance problem already being dealt with. "We have started telling people about the land acquisition deal and we expect the construction to start in 2012," he said.\par \par \uc2 As for flooding, Fauzi said there was little that he could do and he put the blame on global warming.\par \par \uc2 "\b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over weather conditions caused by global warning is something that we can't address, but we can handle the greater chances of flooding with the construction of more sewers," Fauzi said.\par \par \uc2 This year, the city administration repaired 43 sewers in places like in Duren Sawit, Cipinang Indah and Cipinang Besar, all in East Jakarta.\par \par \uc2 "We plan to have repair 73 sewers next year in areas prone to flooding," he said. (map)\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020101230e6cu0000l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgo