eakening of the US dollar and low yields in the advanced countries.\par \par \uc2 So far central banks in the advance countries still tend to keep their \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  relatively low while some emerging markets have increased the rate accompanied by policies for managing capital inflows and stabilizing dollar movement.\par \par \uc2 In the backdrop of the still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial conditions the board of governors of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  still believed the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could grow 6.0 percent in 2010.\par \par \uc2 The achievement was boosted by \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the fourth quarter of 2010 which was predicted to reach 6.1 percent or higher than in the previous quarter.\par \par \uc2 The growth is driven by strong domestic demand especially household consumption and investment. The country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  progress is also boosted by quite solid external performance.\par \par \uc2 For the whole 2010 the NPI would still record a quite big surplus due to continuing strong capital inflows especially direct investment and portfolio.\par \par \uc2 "The foreign currency \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  until the end of December 2010 were recorded at US$96.2 billion or equal to 7.1 months of imports and payments of government foreign debts," he said.\par \par \uc2 In line with the country's strong external \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance the rupiah exchange rate is appreciating with a quite low degree of volatility. Point-to-point the rupiah rose 4.4 percent year-to-date to Rp9,100 per US dollar with lower volatility.\par \par \uc2 To manage capital inflows and stabilize the rupiah exchange rate \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has intervened in foreign currency trading and accumulated foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  to boost positive expectation towards the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Relatively the rupiah appreciation has been lower than the appreciation of other currencies in the region and therefore the country's competitive power remains quite competitive, he said.\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020110106e71500008\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
