 are price \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  and natural risks. The remedies are already clear: \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and protection," Windia said.\par \par \uc2 "Around 60 percent of profits go to traders instead of farmers," added Windia.\par \par \uc2 Agriculture has been a weak sector that needs full governmental support through price policies, incentives and various \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said.\par \par \uc2 Windia added that he was angered by \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies that burdened local farmers. He also said that the National Land Agency (BPN) worked in "stupid" ways in determining land use. "Fertile land and irrigation centers were developed for other uses including residential areas and other functions," he said.\par \par \uc2 The flood of imported fruits, vegetables and even imported rice and sugar worsened the local agricultural situation.\par \par \uc2 "Currently, Balinese people -- both in urban and rural areas, use and buy imported fruits to make religious offerings and for daily consumption," said Windia.\par \par \uc2 I Made Gianyar, regent of Bangli, admitted it was difficult to boost agriculture in his regency. Bangli is one of the lucrative farming centers producing coffee, cloves, cocoa, vegetables and fruits.\par \par \uc2 "We try hard to support local farmers by planning to establish a regional agency that manages harvests, post-harvest handling and distribution, among others things," the regent said.\par \par \uc2 Windia added that local authorities, both provincial and regional administrations, must work together to develop necessary agricultural infrastructure, including irrigation and other needed support, to help local farmers grow.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020110114e71e0001d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
