\par\par \b \uc2 Reportage: It's time to shine for the blessed bunny\b0\par\par\uc2 Rama Ariadi and Chadni Vasandani, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 1,049 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 January 2011\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2011 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 People in show-business will have a good year with Lady Luck on their sides in the upcoming Year of the Rabbit while the country is predicted to experience higher stability and harmony.\par \par \uc2 With the Year of the Rabbit just hopping around the corner, Indonesians are gearing up to celebrate the Chinese New Year, which falls on Feb. 3 this year, flocking to get their personal fortunes read or to find out about their love-lives and career paths.\par \par \uc2 Madame Arra, who was invited by the Grand Indonesia Shopping Town to open a tarot reading and palmistry stand, was overwhelmed with customers eager to get their fortunes read.\par \par \uc2 "Most of them want to see where their lives are heading in this coming Year of the Rabbit, some specifically ask about their love-lives, but there are also some skeptics who come just to test my ability," she says, adding that consultation time is limited to 20 minutes for each customer to accommodate everyone.\par \par \uc2 The Chinese calendar not only follows the 12-year cycle but characteristics within the cycle are touched by the influences of fire, earth, metal, water and wood, each with a yin (female) form and a yang (male) form. This rabbit year is white yin metal, likely meaning the precious metal of silver will become prominent.\par \par \uc2 In the zodiac's cycle, the rabbit comes fourth. Rabbit years include 1927, 1939, 1951, 1963, 1975, 1987 and 1999 on the more international Gregorian calendar, as opposed to Chinese calendar that pegs 2011 as 4708.\par \par \uc2 So, what is the general outlook for the upcoming Year of the Rabbit?\par \par \uc2 Feng Shui consultant Peter Khoe said the Year of the Rabbit would endow the country with higher stability and harmony compared to the turbulent 2010 Year of the Tiger.\par \par \uc2 "By nature, rabbits are calm, careful, elegant and timid creatures. They tend to avoid violent confrontation and are almost never aggressive when faced with danger. Their strength lies in their ability to act swiftly when in peril, but unlike tigers, they calculate their moves -- just like the saying 'a cunning hare has three exits'," he said during an interview at his home.\par \par \uc2 People born in the Year of the Rabbit are usually trusting and unassuming due to the timid nature associated with the rabbit -- meaning this time around, they must be more careful in terms of delegating their trust.\par \par \uc2 Some well-known rabbits are Ben Affleck, Cameron Diaz, Hugh Grant, Jude Law, Marlon Brando, Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, president George Washington, Sean Penn and William Shakespeare.\par \par \uc2 The rabbit is artistic and fashionable -- good news for the entertainment industry. People in show-business will have a good year with Lady Luck on their side.\par \par \uc2 This coming new year will see a lot of variety in the entertainment industry, with a new crop of stars and a wider selection of genres -- a pleasant change of direction that avid moviegoers and observers would warmly welcome, as 2010 was a rather monotonous year for the sector. Producers seemed to be inclined to merely follow trends and make movies and programs with similar themes.\par \par \uc2 "Directors, producers and filmmakers should take risks and push the boundaries, as most rabbit years are characterized by a surge of creative energy. I expect to see talented newcomers and a plethora of quality entertainment in 2011," said Madame Arra.\par \par \uc2 Looking through a historical lens, the Year of the Rabbit has always been favorable for those concerned with showbiz. Audrey Hepburn made her debut in 1951's An American in Paris, which nabbed six Academy Awards shortly after it premiered in New York.\par \par \uc2 However, there might be a scandal involving one of our local celebrities, which will come as a shock to the entertainment industry, Madame Arra says.\par \par \uc2 With both experts saying that having the Rabbit as the reigning shio (animal sign) for 2011 would endow stability and harmony for this period, does this mean Indonesia could breathe a sigh of relief, after the all the dramas and tragedies that have struck the country?\par \par \uc2 Upon revealing the card that predicts the near future of Indonesia -- the Fool -- Madame Arra said, "This card symbolizes the country's potential, to either turn into ruins or blossom into a developed state. The country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  can grow positively if the political elites are willing to coordinate and cooperate -- not only with each other, but also within the international sphere".\par \par \uc2 The amiable and calculating nature of the rabbit hopefully increases national and international cooperation between governments in 2011.\par \par \uc2 Peter predicted the changes would be gradual, and significant ones would start to take effect around the second trimester and the third trimester of 2011.\par \par \uc2 "The Rabbit of 2011 carries a weak element of wood with it. In order for wood to grow healthy and tall, it needs the support of sunshine [fire] and water -- which will come during the month of the Snake, Horse [May-July], Pig and Rat [November-January 2012]," he says.\par \par \uc2 When asked about the country's political drama, Madame Arra says it is unlikely for President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono to be ousted in 2011.\par \par \uc2 "However, the future seems \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  for our President. It seems he may have to step down before completing his office term in 2014," she warned.\par \par \uc2 Peter predicts that sectors involved with the metal element -- such as banking and the precious metal industry -- will experience substantial growth.\par \par \uc2 Those involved in other sectors associated with earth, wood and water -- such as tourism, construction, architecture and handicrafts -- might want to start tightening up their belts, as this year might prove to be a tough one.\par \par \uc2 Those born in the Year of the Goat, which unfortunately includes the notorious graft convict Gayus H. Tambunan, will receive unexpected luck and windfall gains in terms of wealth this year.\par \par \uc2 But be sure to avoid avarice as the cosmic constellation that rules over goats in 2011 is likely to bring legal disputes and lawsuits.\par \par \uc2 Was it the rabbit's unexpected twist of luck which allowed Gayus to serve a light prison sentence after the whole \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 -mafia brouhaha? Maybe, but if not, at least, you can blame it all on the soothsayers.\par \par \uc2 The writers are interns at The Jakarta Post.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020110130e71u0000e\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
