\par\par \b \uc2 Inflation and fuel  \highlight22\uc2 subsidy \highlight\uc2  cuts amid oil price hikes\b0\par\par\uc2 1,027 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 March 2011\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2011 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Zenathan Adnin Hasannudin , Paris\par \par \uc2 The year 2011 has brought an interesting challenge for the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the form of inflation or price increases of aggregate goods.\par \par \uc2 One major indicator for this challenge is the rise of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) rate from 6.5 percent to 6.75 percent in early February. This was the first change of the BI rate since August 2009 and also gives us signals that in 2011 the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has started to beat the drums of war against inflation.\par \par \uc2 After a quick recovery from the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in 2008, Indonesia has enjoyed an impressive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 4.9 percent in 2009 and 6.0 percent in 2010.\par \par \uc2 However the inflation rate rose much faster from 2.78 percent in 2009 to 6.96 percent in 2010. In January 2011 alone, inflation stood at 0.89 percent due to an extraordinary increase in agriculture products such as rice and chili.\par \par \uc2 Therefore, it seems reasonable that BI, as the guardian of macro and monetary stability, has started\par \par \uc2 to feel inflationary pressures and initiated a tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  characterized by an increase of the BI rate.\par \par \uc2 Another issue in the near future to worry about is the impact of the revolution that occurred in North African countries and the Middle East, which are well known as oil producing countries. Political instability in those regions can trigger volatility in world oil prices.\par \par \uc2 In fact, the price has passed the psychological level of US$100 per barrel at the end of February. This rise in world oil prices and low national oil production will always be an important factor pushing the government to formulate good policies, which includes reduction of the fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  from \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Actually the government already has a plan to reduce energy \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , including oil and electricity by 10-15 percent per year until the year 2014. This scheme includes the elimination of the entire \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in that year.\par \par \uc2 Although based on the report of OECD \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Survey on Indonesia in 2010, the government\par \par \uc2 applies a fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to help the poor so that they can meet their basic needs.\par \par \uc2 However, high fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  will disrupt the signal of changes in prices and may cause \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in investment decision making.\par \par \uc2 Moreover, it will reduce the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  ability to finance development activities because if the world fuel price exceeds the assumption in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government will have to cover the price margin.\par \par \uc2 The other problem is, if the government maintains the fuel price at a low level this will encourage people to consume more and more fuel.\par \par \uc2 It will also reduce the incentive to improve efficiency in energy use or research and utilization of other alternative energy sources. In addition, this \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is misplaced because in fact the cheap fuel price is enjoyed by consumers from the middle and upper classes.\par \par \uc2 In the end we must realize that the increase in the world oil price will force the government to reduce fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 . But after that happens the government will have to face a period of adjustment that brings two important kinds of homework.\par \par \uc2 The first issue pertains to the threat of a slow-down of macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance. History shows that every time the government cuts the fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth slowed.\par \par \uc2 For example, in October 2005 when the price of premium gasoline rose by 87.5 percent from Rp 2,400 per liter to Rp 4,500 per liter as a result of the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  reduction, the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew 5.13 percent, lower than the 2006 and 2007 mark of more than 6.0 percent. This occurred because the increase in fuel prices triggered inflation, and especially a rise of production and distribution costs.\par \par \uc2 After the fuel price rises, the producers could not immediately raise their goods price. They wanted their consumers to continue buying their products even after the fuel price increase.\par \par \uc2 So the wisest choice for entrepreneurs was to cut the number of goods they produced while recalculating the cost of production and planning to increase the price of their products in the next period.\par \par \uc2 In the worse case, it may also be possible to lay off some of their employees to reduce pressure on production costs, which means fuel price hikes can lead to unemployment.\par \par \uc2 To deal with these problems, the government needs to think about strategic steps to shore up both the production of major industrial sectors such as steel, cement and mining as well as in the informal sector such as farming, fishery and also small and medium enterprises.\par \par \uc2 Loans with soft credit rates and simple processes or \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives can help entrepreneurs maintain production without having to lay off their employees.\par \par \uc2 The second homework which is also the most important task for governments is to maintain the purchasing power of the people, especially the poor.\par \par \uc2 It is advisable that the government implement policies that compensate for the decline of the real income of the poorest communities and prevent the poverty rate increase in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Referring to the past experience, direct cash assistance for the community is an example of a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  that can be well accepted by poor people, and has a proven capacity to reduce the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil due to a reduction in fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also practically effective, because the cost can be measured by the government.\par \par \uc2 These two government \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  packages, which compensate for the increase in production costs and also maintain people purchasing power, should be implemented simultaneously with continuous evaluations, so that they can reduce other problems that arise after fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  are lifted.\par \par \uc2 The formulation of appropriate policies becomes more important if the government delays adjusting the world oil price in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Nobody wants to see the cost of subsidizing fuel prices rise more than the formulation of the policies either.\par \par \uc2 This \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is misplaced because in fact the cheap fuel price is enjoyed by consumers from the middle and upper classes.\par \par \uc2 The writer is pursuing a Master's degree in economics at Universite Paris 1, Pantheon-Sorbonne.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020110309e7390000p\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
