ement of promotions and salary.\par \par \uc2 Reporters were left with no clear answers regarding the specific fate of the errant officials.\par \par \uc2 Questioned over the matter by reporters separately on Monday, city secretary Fadjar Panjaitan refused to answer whether the officials had been punished.\par \par \uc2 "Please ask Pak Hasan," he said, referring to Hasan Basri Saleh, the assistant to the governor for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and administrative affairs.\par \par \uc2 But Hasan asked reporters to file the question with the inspectorate's office, which was under Fadjar's authority.\par \par \uc2 The Jakarta administration found there were 1,868 minimarkets and convenience stores, up from the 525 in 2006 when the governor issued the decree imposing a moratorium on new minimarkets, banning city agencies and officials from issuing permits or legal documents to new minimarkets or convenience stores.\par \par \uc2 The decree was issued following a surge in the number of markets.\par \par \uc2 Only 425 stores were operating with licenses, which left 1,443 minimarkets operating without proper licenses.\par \par \uc2 Last month, the city ordered 37 improperly licensed establishments to close because they were located less than 500 meters from traditional markets, which was banned by the bylaw on private markets.\par \par \uc2 Of the 37, only nine had closed as of this week.\par \par \uc2 Previously, Deputy Governor Prijanto had hinted that unlicensed stores might not be closed down if the store owners could produce the documents they currently lacked.\par \par \uc2 Under the bylaw, owners needed to secure a recommendation from subdistrict heads, permits from the \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  Order Agency, the Jakarta Trade Agency and the Jakarta Building Supervision Agency to start a business.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020110531e75v00017\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picsca